sentence_excerpt: Per the patient, that's when her memory started to get fuzzy.

She is tired of "fighting" her end stage 
liver disease and does not feel that she has a good quality of 
life.

It is normal 
to feel tired or "washed out" after surgery, and this feeling 
should improve over the first few days to week.

Her vomiting and abdominal pain has not increased from the past 
weeks, but she just feels more fatigued.

She is 
trying to take her pants off, but feels too weak and tired to do 
so.
